.:: Puzzle 1x7-Level-8-3::.
City: boston, rome, hamburg, prague, san-francisco, berlin, miami
 1. the person traveling to prague is not to the left of the person traveling to berlin##8
 2. the person traveling to miami is in an even position##4
 3. the person traveling to berlin is somewhere to the left of the person traveling to rome##5
 4. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the left or right of the person traveling to berlin##3
 5. the person traveling to prague is on the left or right of the person traveling to berlin##3
 6. the person traveling to miami is not to the right of the person traveling to boston##8
 7. the person traveling to hamburg is somewhere between the person traveling to berlin and the person traveling to rome##7
 8. the person traveling to boston is in an odd position##4
 9. the person traveling to boston is not to the right of the person traveling to hamburg##8
10. the person traveling to berlin is on the right of the person traveling to san-francisco##1

.:: Answer ::.
|         |    1    |    2    |     3      |      4      |   5   |    6    |    7    |
| City   | san-francisco | berlin | prague | miami | boston | hamburg | rome |

